  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "Playing with Planes",
    "overview_subtitle": "Graphing Geometric Figures",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students solve geometry problems using the coordinate plane. They conjecture about graphed polygons and prove their conjectures. Students graph triangles and quadrilaterals using given criteria and calculate distances to solve perimeter, area, and volume problems. They then laean a parallelogram's coordinates without a coordinate grid and write an algebraic expression to solve for its area."
  },
